Doctor Dolittle (1967 - USA)

Adventure / Comedy / Family

starring . . . . Rex Harrison, Samantha Eggar, Anthony Newley, Richard Attenborough
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0061584/


Won 2 Oscars with another 4 Award Wins & 14 Award Nominations

Doctor Dolittle is a world-renowned veterinarian who speaks a wide array of animal languages. He sets off from his home in Puddleby-on-the-Marsh in England to search for the Great Pink Sea Snail. In so doing he and his friends meet such exotic creatures as the Pushme-Pullyu and the Giant Lunar Moth. Over 1,200 live animals were used in the film including dogs, pigs, birds, and even giraffes.
